<font color="#FF0000">SPAM,SPAM,SPAM,SPAM,SPAM!</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 28 19:13:09 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
O.K.  here goes.  Spam is a composition of the finest parts of a four legged animal called a pig. You know the lips,ears, tail. Served up best with eggs and toast. Also good with Mayo on bread. Doc Del doesn't appreciate this fine culinary masterpiece because he eats it with pineapple and fish.  Ugh, I wouldn't like it either served that way.  I suspect he really shish-ke-bobs it over a bbq with pineapple slices in the middle or one of those monsters he like to call fish.<br>
And besides, what's wrong with eatin' toejams?    Again served best between two slices of spam with mayo.<br>
And gunbunny? I personally prefer cannon-cocker. It sound more &quot;macho&quot;, don't you know. But like a certain rabbit on t.v. I &quot;just keep goin' and goin'&quot;.  Cain't deny what you be. We say that a lot over here in the Shenandoah Valley, next to the Blue Ridge Mountains.  Country roads take me home.  We hum that a lot here in Ol' Virginny.too And we sing &quot;O Shenandoah&quot; A LOT. &lt;G&gt;<br>
So Spam,spam,spam,spam,spam,spam.  As the old Monty Python refain goes.<br>
Hi, Doc. Long time no speak. Thought a fish took one of your lures and like the Old Man and the Sea, drug you off to Tahiti or somethin'.  But your gettin' old and I guess we all expect that to happen sooner or later.  I know it will if you keep catching fish that you have to display with a 5 ton frontloader.<br>
Ed, welcome home, brother. Jump right in the water is fine. We enjoy all that comes and post. I hope that clears up any possible misconceptions that you might have about spam. P.S. Ignore Doc Del, he has two problems.<br>
#1. Too much time in the tropical sun.<br>
#2. He's ugly and has to live on an island where normal folks can't see him.
